fr.ign.artiscales.analysis

Class DensificationStudy

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.ign.artiscales.analysis.DensificationStudy

  • public class DensificationStudy
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a workflow in order to help densification studies. They can be asked in French Schémas de Cohérence Territoriale (SCoT). It isolate empty parcels within urban zones (called vacant lot and simulates their densification. If they are too big, it simulates the creation of a whole neighborhood. The output shapefile is called parcelDentCreusesDensified.shp It also simulates the parcels that can be created with the flag parcels on already built parcels. The shapefile containing those parcels is called parcelPossiblyDensified.shp
